              "content": "# Installing OpenSpec Skills for OpenCode\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- [OpenCode.ai](https://opencode.ai) installed\n\n## Installation\n\n### 1. Clone the repository (if not already)\n\n```bash\ngit clone ssh://git@stash.delta.sbrf.ru:7999/airiskhub/ai-risk-hub-inner-skill-hub.git ~/ai-risk-hub-inner-skill-hub\n```\n\nOr if you already have it in IdeaProjects:\n\n```bash\ncp -r ~/IdeaProjects/ai-risk-hub-inner-skill-hub/openspec-skills ~/.config/opencode/skills/openspec-skills\n```\n\n### 2. Restart OpenCode\n\nSkills are automatically discovered from `~/.config/opencode/skills/` — no plugin configuration needed.\n\n## Verification\n\nAsk OpenCode: \"What skills do you have?\" or \"How to use OpenSpec skills?\"\n\n## Available Skills\n\n| Skill | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `openspec-teach` | Primer for the AI agent: skills, change lifecycle, statuses, rules, and request-to-skill mapping |\n| `openspec-explore` | Structured research of the codebase via parallel read-only subagents (`task` + `subagent_type=explore` in opencode). Standalone invocation or prompt-library for `new-spec`/`propose` |\n| `openspec-new-spec` | Create a new service specification |\n| `openspec-propose` | Create a change proposal (change.md) |\n| `openspec-design` | Produce design.md + tasks.md from change.md |\n| `openspec-implement` | Execute tasks.md; runs build/tests/lint before completion |\n| `openspec-apply-change` | Merge an approved change into the service spec (git-based rollback) |\n| `openspec-archive-change` | Archive a completed change |\n\n## Updating\n\nTo update, repeat the copy step or pull changes and copy again:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/ai-risk-hub-inner-skill-hub && git pull && cp -r openspec-skills ~/.config/opencode/skills/openspec-skills\n```\n\n## Structure\n\nThe correct structure is:\n\n```\n~/.config/opencode/skills/openspec-skills/\n└── skills/\n    ├── openspec-teach/\n    ├── openspec-explore/\n    ├── openspec-new-spec/\n    ├── openspec-propose/    # + references/, templates/\n    ├── openspec-design/     # + references/, templates/\n    ├── openspec-implement/\n    ├── openspec-apply-change/\n    └── openspec-archive-change/\n```\n\nКаждый скилл self-contained — все шаблоны (`templates/`) и справочные файлы (`references/`) лежат внутри директории соответствующего скила, согласно Agent Skills Spec.\n\nOpenCode automatically discovers skills in `~/.config/opencode/skills/`.\n",
